                     <hi rend="largeCaps">MARY BROMLEY</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18360919-2222-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18360919-2222-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="violentTheft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18360919-2222-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="robbery"></interp>for a robbery on <persName id="t18360919-name-1167" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1167" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1167" type="surname" value="HALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1167" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360919-2222-offence-1 t18360919-name-1167"></join>Mary Ann Hall</persName>, on the <rs id="t18360919-cd-176" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360919-2222-offence-1 t18360919-cd-176"></join>13th of August</rs>, putting her in fear, and taking from her person, and against her will, 1 shawl, value 5<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; 1 half-crown, and 2 shil<lb></lb>lings; the goods and monies of <persName id="t18360919-name-1168" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1168" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1168" type="surname" value="HALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1168" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360919-2222-offence-1 t18360919-name-1168"></join>George Hall</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360919-name-1169" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1169" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1169" type="surname" value="HALL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1169" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN HALL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of George Hall, a sawyer; he lives at a timber wharf in the Commercial-road. On a Saturday in August, I was passing along Waterloo-road, near the New Cut—I had a cloak on my right arm—I saw the prisoner there, with some men and woman—my cloak touched another young woman, but not the prisoner—she struck me directly several blows on my left eye, and called me dreadful names—I lost my senses for a few minutes—I did not fall down—I fell against a post—when I recovered I missed my shawl off my shoulder, and 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. was gone out of my hand—it was loose in my hand—I was going out to buy a little meat, I never wear a pocket, I always carry my money in my hand—I did not say or do any thing when I missed it—she ill-treated me and kicked me—the people were gone when I came to my senses—I have not seen my shawl or money again—I did not give her in charge till two hours after.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> She gave me in charge at ten o'clock, and said she had lost 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; and when the policeman came up, she said she could not swear I took it out of her hand, but she had lost it—did you not call in names? <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I never spoke to her—I did not give her in charge for two hours after.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360919-name-1170" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1170" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1170" type="surname" value="BABER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1170" type="given" value="SUSAN"></interp>SUSAN BABER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Chi✗ Baber, a shoe-maker. I was passing by the end of Waterloo-road, and saw the prisoner and other peo<lb></lb>ple the prosecutrix was before me—she had a cloak on her right arm, and a shawl on her shoulders—Mrs. Hall's cloak touched one of the females who were passing, but not the prisoner—it pushed against her as she passed as there was a crowd of people passing, and she was pushed nearly off the pavement—the prisoner began abusing her, calling her very ill names, and struck her several times—then she struck her a blow with the right hand in the left eye, and took her shawl off her shoulder with her right hand—she handed the shawl to another female, of the name of Hannah Flynn, and said, "Take this, and I will <hi rend="italic">pitch into her again</hi>," and she struck her</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183609190184"></xptr>
               <p>several times afterwards—I did not know Flynn, but the prisoner called her by that name—I went home then—I afterwards went with Mrs. Hall to the New Cut, and saw the prisoner standing opposite the Victoria Theatre—she was given into custody by Mrs. Hall—she called Mrs. Hall very ill names—Mrs. Hall told her, if she would give up her shawl, she would not give her in charge, but if she did not give it up she would—she made a dreadful oath, and said she had not got the shawl, but she had had the worth of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner. Q.</hi> Did you see me take the shawl? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—I did not interfere at all till Mrs. Hall came to me—she fainted away against my shoulder, and took hold of one of the lamp-posts.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360919-name-1171" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1171" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1171" type="surname" value="HODGSKIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-1171" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS HODGSKIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a policeman. The prisoner was given into my charge between twelve and one o'clock in the morning, in the New Cut, for stealing the shawl—she denied all knowledge of the robbery.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I gave myself in charge. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> She did not; the prose<lb></lb>cutrix gave her in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> The prisoner came up and pushed against me, and called me a <hi rend="italic">bumper</hi>—I said I was no more a <hi rend="italic">bumper</hi> than she was, and she struck against me, and I struck her again—she then gave me in charge of George Smith—he asked if I had robbed her—she said no, she had lost 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., but could not say I robbed her—and between twelve and one o'clock she came and asked me for her shawl—I said I had not got it—she said, "I shall give you in charge; I can't swear to the money, but I can swear to the shawl;" and went for a policeman.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
